ďťż{
  "Product and Quotient Rules": "Reglas del producto y del quotient",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "Esta lecciĂłn cubre las medidas fundamentales del centro utilizadas para analizar y resumir conjuntos de datos. AprenderĂĄ cĂłmo calcular y aplicar la media, mediana y modo, y entenderĂĄ cuĂĄndo cada uno es mĂĄs apropiado.",
  "What is d/dx[x^3 * e^x] using the product rule?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es d/dx[x^3 * e^x] usando la regla del producto?",
  "Product rule: d/dx[x^3 * e^x] = 3x^2 * e^x + x^3 * e^x = e^x(3x^2 + x^3) = e^x(x^3 + 3x^2).": "Regla del producto: d/dx[x^3 * e^x] = 3x^2 * e^x + x^3 * e^x = e^x(3x^2 + x^3) = e^x(x^3 + 3x^2).",
  "What is d/dx[(3x + 2)(x^2 - 1)]?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es d/dx[(3x + 2)(x^2 - 1)]?",
  "Product rule: (3)(x^2-1) + (3x+2)(2x) = 3x^2 - 3 + 6x^2 + 4x = 9x^2 + 4x - 3.": "Regla del producto: (3) x^2-1) + (3x+2)(2x) = 3x^2 - 3 + 6x^2 + 4x = 9x^2 + 4x - 3.",
  "What is d/dx[(2x - 5)/(x + 3)] using the quotient rule?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es d/dx[(2x - 5)/(x + 3)] usando la regla del cociente?",
  "Quotient rule: [2(x+3) - (2x-5)(1)]/(x+3)^2 = [2x + 6 - 2x + 5]/(x+3)^2 = 11/(x+3)^2.": "[2(x+3) - (2x-5)(1)]/(x+3)^2 = [2x + 6 - 2x + 5]/(x+3)^2 = 11/(x+3)^2.",
  "What is d/dx[sin(x) * cos(x)]?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es d/dx[sin(x) * cos(x)]?",
  "Product rule: cos(x)*cos(x) + sin(x)*(-sin(x)) = cos^2(x) - sin^2(x). This is also equal to cos(2x) by the double angle identity.": "Regla del producto: cos(x)*cos(x) + sin(x)*(-sin(x)) = cos^2(x) - sin^2(x). Esto tambiĂŠn es igual a cos(2x) por la identidad de doble ĂĄngulo.",
  "What is d/dx[x * sqrt(x)] simplified?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es d/dx[x * sqrt(x)] simplificado?",
  "Product rule: (1)(sqrt(x)) + x * (1/(2sqrt(x))) = sqrt(x) + x/(2sqrt(x)) = sqrt(x) + sqrt(x)/2 = (3/2)sqrt(x). Alternatively, x*sqrt(x) = x^(3/2), so d/dx = (3/2)x^(1/2) = (3/2)sqrt(x).": "Regla del producto: 1) sqrt(x)) + x * (1/(2sqrt(x))) = sqrt(x) + x/(2sqrt(x)) = sqrt(x) + sqrt(x)/2 = (3/2)sqrt(x). Alternativamente, x*sqrt(x) = x^(3/2), asĂ­ d/dx = (3/2)x^(1/2) = (3/2)sqrt(x).",
  "What is d/dx[e^x / x^2] using the quotient rule?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es d/dx[e^x / x^2] usando la regla del cociente?",
  "Quotient rule: [e^x * x^2 - e^x * 2x]/x^4 = e^x(x^2 - 2x)/x^4 = e^x * x(x-2)/x^4 = e^x(x-2)/x^3.": "Regla de clasificaciĂłn: [e^x * x^2 - e^x * 2x]/x^4 = e^x(x^2 - 2x)/x^4 = e^x * x(x-2)/x^4 = e^x(x-2)/x^3.",
  "If f(x) = (x + 1)(x^2 + 3), what is f'(0)?": "Si f(x) = (x + 1)(x^2 + 3), ÂżquĂŠ es f'(0)?",
  "f'(x) = (1)(x^2+3) + (x+1)(2x) = x^2 + 3 + 2x^2 + 2x = 3x^2 + 2x + 3. At x = 0: f'(0) = 0 + 0 + 3 = 3.": "f'(x) = (1) x^2+3) + (x+1)(2x) = x^2 + 3 + 2x^2 + 2x = 3x^2 + 2x + 3. A x = 0: f'(0) = 0 + 0 + 3 = 3.",
  "What is d/dx[tan(x)] using sin(x)/cos(x) and the quotient rule?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es d/dx[tan(x)] usando sin(x)/cos(x) y la regla del cociente?",
  "d/dx[sin(x)/cos(x)] = [cos(x)*cos(x) - sin(x)*(-sin(x))]/cos^2(x) = [cos^2(x) + sin^2(x)]/cos^2(x) = 1/cos^2(x) = sec^2(x).": "d/dx[sin(x)/cos(x)] = [cos(x)*cos(x) - sin(x)*(-sin(x))]/cos^2(x) = [cos^2(x) + sin^2(x)]/cos^2(x) = 1/cos^2(x) = sec^2(x).",
  "What is d/dx[x^2/(x + 4)] evaluated at x = 1?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es d/dx[x^2/(x + 4)] evaluado en x = 1?",
  "Quotient rule: [2x(x+4) - x^2(1)]/(x+4)^2 = (2x^2 + 8x - x^2)/(x+4)^2 = (x^2 + 8x)/(x+4)^2. At x = 1: (1+8)/25 = 9/25.": "Regla de clasificaciĂłn: [2x(x+4) - x^2(1)]/(x+4)^2 = (2x^2 + 8x - x^2)/(x+4)^2 = (x^2 + 8x)/(x+4)^2. A x = 1: (1+8)/25 = 9/25.",
  "What is d/dx[(x^2 + 1)(x^3 - 2x)] evaluated at x = 1?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es d/dx[(x^2 + 1)(x^3 - 2x)] evaluado en x = 1?",
  "Product rule: 2x(x^3-2x) + (x^2+1)(3x^2-2). At x = 1: 2(1)(1-2) + (2)(3-2) = 2(-1) + 2(1) = -2 + 2 = 0.": "Regla del producto: 2x(x^3-2x) + (x^2+1)(3x^2-2). A x = 1: 2(1)-1-2) + (2)3-2 = 2-1) + 2(1) = -2 + 2 = 0.",
  "What is meant by 'numerator' in the context of the quotient rule?": "ÂżQuĂŠ se entiende por \"numerador\" en el contexto de la regla del cociente?",
  "In a fraction f(x)/g(x), the numerator is f(x) -- the top function. In the quotient rule, you differentiate the numerator and multiply by the denominator, then subtract.": "En una fracciĂłn f(x)/g(x), el numerador es f(x) -- la funciĂłn superior. En la regla del cociente, diferencia el numerador y se multiplica por el denominador, luego resta.",
  "What is 'denominator' in the context of the quotient rule?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es 'denominador' en el contexto de la regla del cociente?",
  "In a fraction f(x)/g(x), the denominator is g(x) -- the bottom function. In the quotient rule, the denominator squared appears in the result: [f'g - fg']/g^2.": "En una fracciĂłn f(x)/g(x), el denominador es g(x) -- la funciĂłn inferior. En la regla del cociente, el denominador al cuadrado aparece en el resultado: [f'g - fg']/g^2.",
  "What is the 'secant function' sec(x)?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es la 'funciĂłn secante' sec(x)?",
  "The secant function is defined as sec(x) = 1/cos(x). It appears frequently in derivatives: for example, d/dx[tan(x)] = sec^2(x), which can be derived using the quotient rule on sin(x)/cos(x).": "La funciĂłn secante se define como sec(x) = 1/cos(x). Aparece con frecuencia en derivados: por ejemplo, d/dx[tan(x)] = sec^2(x), que se puede derivar utilizando la regla del cociente sobre sin(x)/cos(x).",
  "What is meant by 'undefined' in the context of the quotient rule?": "ÂżQuĂŠ se entiende por 'indefinido' en el contexto de la regla del cociente?",
  "When applying the quotient rule, the result is undefined wherever the denominator g(x) = 0, since division by zero is not defined. These points may correspond to vertical asymptotes or holes in the function.": "Cuando se aplica la regla del cociente, el resultado no se define donde el denominador g(x) = 0, ya que no se define la divisiĂłn por cero. Estos puntos pueden corresponder a asymptotes verticales u agujeros en la funciĂłn.",
  "What is 'algebraic manipulation' in the context of simplifying derivatives?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es la \"manipulaciĂłn algebraica\" en el contexto de la simplificaciĂłn de los derivados?",
  "Algebraic manipulation involves rewriting expressions using techniques like expanding products, factoring, combining like terms, and canceling common factors to simplify derivative results.": "La manipulaciĂłn algebraica implica reescribir expresiones usando tĂŠcnicas como expandir productos, factorizar, combinar tĂŠrminos similares y cancelar factores comunes para simplificar los resultados derivados.",
  "A population of fish in a lake is modeled by P(t) = 5000t/(t + 10) fish, where t is years. A wildlife biologist wants to know the growth rate at t = 15 years. What is P'(15)?": "Una poblaciĂłn de peces en un lago es modelada por P(t) = 5000t/(t + 10) peces, donde t es aĂąos. Un biĂłlogo de la vida silvestre quiere saber la tasa de crecimiento en t = 15 aĂąos. ÂżQuĂŠ es P'(15)?",
  "P'(t) = [5000(t+10) - 5000t]/(t+10)^2 = 50000/(t+10)^2. At t = 15: P'(15) = 50000/625 = 80 fish per year.": "P'(t) = [5000(t+10) - 5000t]/(t+10)^2 = 50000/(t+10)^2. En t = 15: P'(15) = 50000/625 = 80 peces por aĂąo.",
  "A car's fuel efficiency in mpg is modeled by E(v) = v * (60 - 0.5v)/(v + 10) where v is speed in mph. Using the quotient rule, what is E'(30)?": "La eficiencia de combustible de un coche en mpg es modelada por E(v) = v * (60 - 0.5v)/(v + 10) donde v es velocidad en mph. Usando la regla del cociente, ÂżquĂŠ es E'(30)?",
  "First simplify: E(v) = (60v - 0.5v^2)/(v+10). E'(v) = [(60-v)(v+10) - (60v-0.5v^2)(1)]/(v+10)^2. At v=30: numerator = (30)(40) - (1800-450) = 1200 - 1350 = -150. Wait -- let me recalculate: (60-30)(40) - (1800-450) = 1200-1350 = -150. E'(30) = -150/1600. Let me recheck the problem. Actually E'(30) = [(60-v)(v+10) - (60v-0.5v^2)]/(v+10)^2 = [600+60*10-v^2-10v-60v+0.5v^2]/(v+10)^2. This needs careful expansion.": "En primer lugar, simplificar: E(v) = (60v - 0.5v^2)/(v+10). E'(v) = [(60-v)(v+10) - (60v-0.5v^2)(1)]/(v+10)^2. En v=30: numerador = (30)(40) - (1800-450) = 1200 - 1350 = -150. Espera - dĂŠjame volver a calcular: (60-30)(40) - (1800-450) = 1200-1350 = -150. E'(30) = -150/1600. PermĂ­tanme revisar el problema. En realidad E'(30) = [(60-v)(v+10) - (60v-0.5v^2)]/(v+10)^2 = [600+60*10-v^2-10v+60v+0.5v^2]/(v+10)^2.",
  "A real estate agent models home prices as P(t) = (200 + 5t)(1000 + 50t) dollars, where t is years from now. What is the rate of increase in home prices at t = 0?": "Un agente inmobiliario modela los precios de la vivienda como P(t) = (200 + 5t) (1000 + 50t) dĂłlares, donde t es de aĂąos a partir de ahora. ÂżCuĂĄl es la tasa de aumento en los precios de la vivienda en t = 0?",
  "P'(t) = 5(1000+50t) + (200+5t)(50) = 5000+250t + 10000+250t = 15000+500t. At t = 0: P'(0) = $15,000 per year.": "P'(t) = 5(1000+50t) + (200+5t)(50) = 5000+250t + 10000+250t = 15000+500t. A t = 0: P'(0) = 15.000 dĂłlares anuales.",
  "A physics experiment measures the ratio of kinetic to potential energy as R(h) = (20 - h)/h for a falling object at height h meters. What is R'(5)?": "Un experimento de fĂ­sica mide la proporciĂłn de energĂ­a cinĂŠtica a potencial como R(h) = (20 - h)/h para un objeto que cae a la altura h metros. ÂżQuĂŠ es R'(5)?",
  "R(h) = (20-h)/h = 20/h - 1. So R'(h) = -20/h^2. At h = 5: R'(5) = -20/25 = -4/5. Alternatively, quotient rule: [(-1)(h) - (20-h)(1)]/h^2 = [-h-20+h]/h^2 = -20/h^2.": "R(h) = (20-h)/h = 20/h - 1. AsĂ­ que R'(h) = -20/h^2. En h = 5: R'(5) = -20/25 = -4/5. Alternativamente, regla del cociente: [(-1)(h) - (20-h)(1)]/h^2 = [-h-20+h]/h^2 = -20/h^2.",
  "A marketing firm models ad revenue as R(x) = x * sqrt(100 - x) thousand dollars, where x is thousands spent on advertising. What is the marginal revenue at x = 36?": "Una empresa de marketing modelos de ingresos publicitarios como R(x) = x * sqrt(100 - x) miles de dĂłlares, donde x se gastan miles en publicidad. ÂżCuĂĄl es el ingreso marginal en x = 36?",
  "R'(x) = sqrt(100-x) + x * (-1)/(2*sqrt(100-x)) = sqrt(100-x) - x/(2*sqrt(100-x)). At x = 36: sqrt(64) = 8, so R'(36) = 8 - 36/16 = 8 - 2.25 = 5.75 thousand dollars per thousand spent.": "R'(x) = sqrt(100-x) + x * (-1)/(2*sqrt(100-x)) = sqrt(100-x) - x/(2*sqrt(100-x)). A x = 36: sqrt(64) = 8, asĂ­ que R'(36) = 8 - 36/16 = 8 - 2,25 = 5,75 mil dĂłlares por mil gastados."
}